  "chunk_index": 31,
  "summary": "In a common room, Genavieve announces to a group of students, including Mr. Chandra Lal, Gene, and Ahmed Ali, that she is certain Nigel Chapman killed Silvia. She claims she overheard Nigel in Patricia Lane's room explaining that his father was a murderer and why Nigel had changed his name. While some students speculate on Nigel's motives, Leonard Betson reacts angrily to the accusations.\n\nAt a police station, Nigel provides a statement to Inspector Sharp, explaining that Patricia Lane is in a state of mental instability and cannot remember when she last saw a morphine bottle. During their interview, a constable receives an agitated call from Patricia; she claims to know who took the bottle from her handkerchief drawer, but the line goes dead before she can identify the person.\n\nInspector Sharp and Nigel travel to 26 Walnut Street, where they find Patricia Ryan dead on her floor. Sharp determines she was killed by a blow to the back of the head with a marble \"Luzern Lion\" paperweight wrapped in a wool sock. Nigel becomes distraught, noting that the sock belonged to him. To establish a timeline, Sharp questions Jeremiah, who states that between 6:00 and 6:35, Nigel, Mrs. Habberd, and Valerie Hobhouse were absent. Nigel left at 6:00 looking agitated, and Valerie left at 6:00 dressed semi-formally. Since Patricia's call occurred at 6:08, Sharp notes that Nigel, Valerie, and Mrs. Habberd are the primary individuals whose whereabouts are unaccounted for during the time of the call.",
